# DirectTip — Firebase Setup Guide

The app now has a full Firebase sync layer built in, but it ships **disabled**.
Until you paste your config in, everything runs exactly like before (localStorage
only), so you can deploy this version today with zero risk.

The architecture is **local-first**: localStorage stays the instant source of
truth the UI reads from, and Firestore syncs in the background. That's why the
app never shows loading spinners and keeps working offline as a PWA.

---

## Step 1 — Create the Firebase project (~3 min)

1. Go to https://console.firebase.google.com and click **Add project**
2. Name it `directtip` (or anything). Google Analytics: optional, disable to keep it simple.
3. Once created, click the **web icon `</>`** on the project overview page to add a web app
4. Nickname: `DirectTip PWA`. Do NOT check "Firebase Hosting" (you're on GitHub Pages).
5. Firebase shows you a `firebaseConfig` object — **copy it**

## Step 2 — Paste the config into index.html

Open `index.html`, find this block near the top of the main `<script>`:

```js
const FIREBASE_CONFIG = {
  apiKey: "PASTE_ME",
  ...
};
```

Replace it with your real values. The app detects a real config automatically —
no other switch to flip.

> **Is it safe to commit this to a public GitHub repo? Yes.** The Firebase web
> config is an identifier, not a secret — every visitor's browser needs it to
> talk to Firebase. Your security boundary is the **rules** in Step 4, not the
> config. (People trip on this constantly.)

## Step 3 — Enable Authentication

In the Firebase console → **Build → Authentication → Get started**:

1. Enable **Email/Password** (used by worker + tipper signups)
2. Enable **Anonymous** (used silently so guests can send tips)

## Step 4 — Create Firestore + security rules

Console → **Build → Firestore Database → Create database**:

1. Choose **Production mode** (locked by default — good)
2. Pick a US region (e.g. `us-central1`) — closest to you and can't be changed later

Then go to the **Rules** tab and replace everything with:

```
rules_version = '2';
service cloud.firestore {
  match /databases/{database}/documents {

    // Worker profiles: public directory (that's the point — customers
    // look workers up). Only real (non-anonymous) accounts can claim a
    // handle, and only the owner can edit their profile afterwards.
    match /workers/{handle} {
      allow read: if true;
      allow create: if request.auth != null
        && request.auth.token.firebase.sign_in_provider != 'anonymous'
        && request.resource.data.uid == request.auth.uid;
      allow update: if request.auth != null
        && resource.data.uid == request.auth.uid;
      allow delete: if false;
    }

    // Tips: anyone signed in (including anonymous guests) can create one,
    // with basic sanity limits. No edits or deletes ever.
    match /tips/{tipId} {
      allow create: if request.auth != null
        && request.resource.data.amount is number
        && request.resource.data.amount > 0
        && request.resource.data.amount <= 500
        && request.resource.data.to is string;
      allow read: if request.auth != null;
      allow update, delete: if false;
    }
  }
}
```

Click **Publish**.

## Step 5 — Deploy

Commit + push `index.html` and `sw.js` to the repo. GitHub Pages picks it up
in a minute or two. Because the service worker cache bumped to `directtip-v2`,
existing installs (including your iPhone PWA) will pull the new version on
their next launch.

