## What changes once Firebase is live

| Feature | Before (local-only) | After (Firebase) |
|---|---|---|
| Worker signup | Fake demo auth | Real email/password accounts |
| Handle availability | Checked on this device only | Checked globally |
| Typing an ID to tip | Only finds workers created on *your* phone | Finds any worker, any device |
| QR scan | Works via profile embedded in the QR itself | Same, plus cloud lookup |
| Tips | Stay on the sender's phone | Land in the worker's real feed/earnings |
| Guest tipping | Works | Works (silent anonymous auth) |

## Known limitations / future hardening

- **Tip reads are open to any signed-in user.** Locking reads down to just the
  recipient requires storing the recipient's `uid` on each tip (`toUid`) and
  querying by that — Firestore rules can't do per-document lookups on list
  queries. Fine for MVP; worth doing before real money flows.
- **Payments are still simulated.** The "processing" screen doesn't move money.
  Stripe Connect is the standard way to do direct worker payouts when you get there.
- **Check-in GPS** still writes `lat: 0, lng: 0` — wiring real coordinates into
  the worker doc on check-in is a natural next feature (one `setDoc` + a
  Firestore query by geohash or a simple client-side distance filter).
- The old demo login fallback ("any email logs in as marcus") only exists in
  local-only mode and disappears entirely once Firebase is enabled.
